independent_work.et:
.
To pass the course the student is expected to
*	Read and respond to the texts required in the course;
*	Independent creative translation of a chosen text;
*	Feedback to your peers' translation;
*	Pass the final exam.

More specific guidelines for independent work will be given during the course.
.

description.et:
Combined final exam: oral discussion based on the written analysis of a case of translation - can provide up to 50 points (up to 25 points for the written analysis and up to 25 for the oral discussion).

Assessment criteria for the analysis and discussion: 
- demonstration of the ability to choose and apply relevant concepts and conceptual frameworks acquired during the course in the analysis of translation; 
- clear and logical presentation of the analysis both in written and oral form; 
- ability to engage in the discussion about issues discussed during the course as related to one's own analysis.

grade_evaluation.et:
.
The final grade will be composed of the following components:
*	Reading and responding to obligatory texts can provide up to 25 points;
*	Producing a translation of a chosen text can provide up to 20 points;
*	Giving feedback to your peers' translation can provide up to 5 points;
*	Passing the final combined (written + oral) exam can provide up to 50 points.

It is possible to receive bonus points for a remarkably good completion of some task.

The final grade for the course will be acquired by converting the result received on the 100-point scale into alphabetical grade (91-100 points: A, 81-90 points: B, 71-80 points: C, 61-70 points: D, 51-60 points: E, less than 51 points: F)
.
